The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices as of 1:57 p.m. local time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.4 percent to 20,195.40. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 0.2 percent to 2,609.79.  Mining and industrial shares dropped after U.S. stocks
declined, said Francisco Miranda, an analyst at Lima-based
investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian exploration
company, fell 4.6 percent to 41 cents.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. gold producer with a mine in Peru, slid 2.8 percent
to $1.05.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor
for Caterpillar Inc., dropped 1.3 percent to 2.35 soles.  Corp.
Aceros Arequipa SA (CORA)  (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker,
fell 1.5 percent to 1.97 soles.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), the countryâ€™s biggest
producer of the metal, rose 0.8 percent to $32.22 after futures
